In July 2010, it was reported by ''[[The_Scotsman|The Scotsman]]'' newspaper that Rhodes was being considered for selection by the [[Scotland_national_under-21_football_team|Scotland national under-21 football team]].<ref name = "scotland"/> Rhodes is eligible to play for Scotland because he attended school there for more than five years, while [[Andy_Rhodes|his father]] played for Scottish clubs.<ref name = "scotland">{{cite news |url=http://www.scotsman.com/football/Scotland-manager-defends-courting-players.6439067.jp |title=Scotland manager defends courting players from south of the Border |work=[[The_Scotsman|The Scotsman]] |date=26 July 2010 |accessdate=29 August 2010 |last=Wright |publisher=Johnston Press|first=Angus}}</ref> He received his first call-up to the Scotland under-21 squad in November 2010, but was immediately withdrawn because Huddersfield were due to play an [[FA_Cup|FA Cup]] replay against [[Cambridge_United_F.C.|Cambridge United]] on the day before the under-21 match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.examiner.co.uk/huddersfield-town-fc/huddersfield-town-news/2010/11/09/huddersfield-town-boss-on-squad-tactics-v-rotherham-utd-86081-27622344/#ixzz1a25Wd2hD|title=Huddersfield Town boss on squad tactics v Rotherham Utd|work=[[Huddersfield_Daily_Examiner|Huddersfield Daily Examiner]]|first=Mel|last=Booth|publisher=[[Trinity_Mirror|Trinity Mirror]]|date=9 November 2010|accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref>

Rhodes eventually made his debut for Scotland under-21s on 24 March 2011, in a 1–0 loss to [[Belgium_national_under-21_football_team|Belgium]] in [[Deinze|Deinze]]. He made his home debut  on 10 August 2011, in the 3–0 win over [[Norway_national_under-21_football_team|Norway]] at [[St._Mirren_Park|St. Mirren Park]]. He scored his first goals for Scotland with a [[hat-trick|hat-trick]] in a 5–1 win against [[Luxembourg_national_under-21_football_team|Luxembourg]] at [[Stade_Josy_Barthel|Stade Josy Barthel]], [[Luxembourg_(city)|Luxembourg City]] on 6 October 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/scottish_fa_news.cfm?page=128&newsID=8667|publisher=Scottish Football Association|work=|date=6 October 2011|accessdate=6 October 2011|title=Rhodes grabs hat-trick in U21 romp}}</ref> Four days later, Rhodes scored both of the Scotland goals in a 2–2 draw against [[Austria_national_under-21_football_team|Austria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/scotland/15250973.stm|title=Scotland U21 2–2 Austria U21|work=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=10 October 2011|accessdate=10 October 2011}}</ref> He scored in Scotland's 2–1 victory over Holland in an U21 qualifier for the 2013 U21 European Championships. After only 6 appearances, he is the joint all-time top scorer for the Scotland U21 team.

